==Synopsis==
<code>\edef &lt;command&gt; {&lt;replacement-text&gt;}</code>

==Description==
<code>\edef</code> is similar to [[TeX/def|\def]] in that it allows you to define new macros or replace an existing macro.  The significant defining difference between <code>\edef</code> and [[TeX/def|\def]] is that <code>\edef</code> expands macros at definition time, rather than saving them for later.  This difference allows <code>\edef</code> to be used to append new information to a macro, for example:
<source lang="latex">
\edef\@test{A}
\edef\@test{\@test B}
\edef\@test{\@test C}

\@test
</source>
results in the output "ABC".  Attempting to do this example with [[TeX/def|\def]] instead will result in the error "TeX capacity exceeded, sorry".  This behavior can be useful in loops that compile a string of information, but do not end up outputting the information directly.

